title: Rose
desc: When ordinary shop-worker Rose Tyler meets a mysterious stranger called the Doctor she is drawn into his strange and dangerous world; her life will never be the same again.

title: The End of the World
desc: The Doctor takes Rose to the year 5 billion to witness the destruction of the Earth.

title: The Unquiet Dead
desc: The Doctor has great expectations for his latest adventure when he and Rose join forces with Charles Dickens to investigate a mysterious plague of zombies.

title: Aliens of London
desc: The Doctor returns Rose to her own time - well, sort of - but her family reunion is ruined when a spaceship crashes in the middle of London. What is the origin of the spaceship, and where has the Prime Minister gone in this time of crisis?

title: World War Three
desc: The Slitheen have infiltrated Parliament and have the Doctor and his friends trapped as the Doctor works to prevent them from starting World War Three.

title: Dalek
desc: The TARDIS is drawn to an alien museum deep below the Utah desert, where a ruthless billionaire keeps prisoner the last of the Doctor's most fearsome enemies.

title: The Long Game
desc: In the year 200,000 the Doctor discovers that a satellite with a dark secret is controlling humanity and slowing its development.

title: Father's Day
desc: Rose asks The Doctor to take her to 1987, on the day her father was killed.

title: The Empty Child
desc: When a spaceship crashes in the middle of the London Blitz the Doctor, Rose and the enigmatic Captain Jack Harkness find themselves investigating a plague of physical injuries and a little boy in a gas mask.

title: The Doctor Dances
desc: The gas mask zombies are on the rise as the plague spreads across war-torn London.

title: Boom Town
desc: Stopping off in present-day Cardiff to recharge the TARDIS, The Doctor, Rose and Jack meet up with Mickey and encounter an old foe in the midst of hatching a scheme that could destroy the entire planet.

title: Bad Wolf
desc: The Doctor, Rose and Jack are separated and forced to compete in twisted and deadly games on the Game Station.

title: The Parting of the Ways
desc: As the Dalek fleet begin their attack on the Earth, the Doctor and his allies make one final stand.

title: The Christmas Invasion
desc: It's Christmas Eve, but this is to be a far from silent night - the cruel Sycorax have come to Earth to enslave mankind and, as ever, only The Doctor can stop them. Unfortunately, he's lying in a coma in Jackie's home...

title: New Earth
desc: The Doctor and Rose arrive on New Earth and meet old friends and enemies in a hospital which can cure every disease. But the cures come at a terrible cost.

title: Tooth and Claw
desc: The Doctor and Rose are transported to 19th Century Scotland, where they meet Queen Victoria, and try to protect her from a ravenous werewolf and a band of assassinating warrior-monks

title: School Reunion
desc: The Krillitanes - aliens with a mix-and-match physiology - are trying to crack the 'God-Maker', a paradigm to give them ultimate power. They are using children as a computer, and only the Doctor and Rose, re-united with Sarah Jane Smith and K9 can prevent them from becoming masters of time and space.

title: The Girl in the Fireplace
desc: The Doctor, Mickey and Rose land on a spaceship in the 51st century only to find 18th century Versailles on board, the time of Madame De Pompadour! To find out what's going on the Doctor must enter Versailles and save Madame De Popmpadour but it turns into an emotional roller coaster for the Doctor.

title: Rise of the Cybermen
desc: The TARDIS crash lands in London on a parallel world, where Rose's dad is still alive, people are disappearing off the streets and one of the Doctor's deadliest enemies is about to be reborn.

title: The Age of Steel
desc: The Cybermen take control of London as the population is enslaved and the Doctor and his friends become fugitives.

title: The Idiot's Lantern
desc: As the coronation of Elizabeth II nears, the streets of London live in fear. Faceless people are stolen from their homes in the night and something evil is lurking in the television.

title: The Impossible Planet
desc: When the Doctor and Rose become stranded on a planet orbiting a black hole, they find a human expedition crew and their servants, the Ood, being terrorised by the Devil.

title: The Satan Pit
desc: The Doctor risks his life to investigate the pit and is forced to make a terrible decision, while Rose and the crew fend for their lives against the Legion of the Beast.

title: Love & Monsters
desc: Elton Pope is an ordinary man intrigued by the world of the Doctor. When he and fellow enthusiasts - L.I.N.D.A. - meet the mysterious Victor Kennedy, their lives will never be the same again.

title: Fear Her
desc: When children vanish into thin air in 2012 London, the Doctor and Rose find the answers in a seemingly ordinary household and a girl whose drawings can come to life.

title: Army of Ghosts
desc: When ghosts of loved ones appear all over the world the Doctor traces the phenomena to the Torchwood Tower, where some old friends and enemies are waiting.

title: Doomsday
desc: Earth becomes a battleground for the Daleks and the Cybermen. With the whole planet at stake and the Genesis Ark activated, how much will the Doctor sacrifice in order to end the war?

title: The Runaway Bride
desc: The Doctor is baffled when a young woman is transported to the TARDIS on her wedding day, and attempts to find out how she is connected to an alien plot to destroy Earth.

title: Smith and Jones
desc: When the hospital she works at is transported to the moon, medical student Martha Jones joins forces with The Doctor to hunt down an alien fugitive before the oxygen runs out.

title: The Shakespeare Code
desc: The Doctor takes Martha to London in 1599, where William Shakespeare's new play is being used by three witches in an evil plan.

title: Gridlock
desc: The Doctor takes Martha to New Earth, where she is kidnapped by two carjackers and taken to an underground Motorway, where the remainder of humanity on the planet live in perpetual gridlock.

title: Daleks in Manhattan
desc: The Doctor and Martha travel to New York in 1930, where people have been mysteriously vanishing from the streets, and an old enemy resurfaces.

title: Evolution of the Daleks
desc: Concluding part to Daleks in Manhattan. In 1930s New York, the Daleks' plan is in full force. Faced with the cyborgs' most evil and dangerous scheme yet, will the Doctor and Martha be able to defeat their greatest opponents?

title: The Lazarus Experiment
desc: The famous Dr Lazarus has appeared to discover the secret of eternal youth - but do his experiments hide a sinister secret?
On a spaceship headed straight for the centre of the sun, the Doctor only has 42 minutes to save Martha and the ship's crew from an inevitable doom.

title: Human Nature
desc: In 1913, Martha watches in jealousy from afar as The Doctor learns what it is to be human and to fall in love with the local school nurse, Joan Redfern.

title: The Family of Blood
desc: The Doctor must deal with the repercussions of his decision to become human, as The Family Of Blood unveil themselves...

title: Blink
desc: Sally Sparrow receives a cryptic message from the Doctor about a mysterious new enemy species that is after the TARDIS.

title: Utopia
desc: Soon after bumping into old friend Jack Harkness, Martha and The Doctor head off to Malcassairo, a distant planet where an old professor will do anything he can to keep his people alive...

title: The Sound of Drums
desc: The Doctor, Martha and Jack return to the 21st Century eighteen months after the Doctor and Martha left. They find they've missed the election, and the new Prime Minister, Harold Saxon, is someone they've met before by another name.

title: Last of the Time Lords
desc: It's been a year since The Master unleashed the mysterious Toclafane onto Earth. With the human race and The Doctor enslaved under The Master's control, Martha Jones is the only person that can help stop the evil Time Lord.

title: Voyage of the Damned
desc: A spacecraft set on an apocalyptic collision course with Earth, a host of killer robot angels and an evil severed headed mastermind - it's just another Christmas for the Doctor... 2007 Christmas special guest starring Kylie Minogue.

title: Partners in Crime
desc: With a new weight-loss pill tested in London by Adipose Industries, The Doctor goes to investigate the sinister truth behind the product, only to find out that his old friend Donna Noble is investigating as well.

title: The Fires of Pompeii
desc: Instead of Rome, The Doctor and Donna Noble end up visiting Pompeii in AD 79, on the eve of the catastrophic eruption of Mount Vesuvius. Before anyone even knew it was actually a volcano, the entire city is doomed for destruction.

title: Planet of the Ood
desc: Finding themselves on the Ood-Sphere planet in the 42nd century, The Doctor and Donna discover the truth over the Ood's willingness to serve humankind.

title: The Sontaran Stratagem
desc: UNIT's newest recruit Martha Jones enlists The Doctor's help to investigate kid genius Luke Rattigan and his ATMOS system that is used in every car on Earth.

title: The Poison Sky
desc: With planet Earth choking under the poison sky, the Doctor must stop the Sontarans' threat to the planet.

title: The Doctor's Daughter
desc: Caught in the middle of a war between the Humans and the Hath in the planet Messaline, the Doctor finds himself once again a father.

title: The Unicorn and the Wasp
desc: With a 1926 dinner party turning into a murder mystery, The Doctor and Donna Noble get the chance to meet Agatha Christie on the eve of her well-known 9-days disappearance.

title: Silence in the Library
desc: The Doctor and Donna join a group of archaeologists at a 51st century library. What caused the library to become abandoned? What are the Nodes? And what links the library to one little girl? All they have is one warning - count the shadows.

title: Forest of the Dead
desc: With the library darkening, the Doctor takes on the Vashta Nerada while figuring out what links River Song to his future. Meanwhile, Donna finds out the mystery of Dr. Moon and the Girl.

title: Midnight
desc: As part of a well-deserved holiday, the Doctor takes a tour on a planet called Midnight. Little does he know that something is knocking on the walls, although the planet shouldn't be inhabited. Soon the passengers begin to panic when one of them is possessed.

title: Turn Left
desc: What would happen if Donna never met the Doctor? How would Earth handle the Racnoss, the falling Titanic or the Sontarans? Aided by a familiar blonde time traveler, Donna corrects the alternate time line from happening.

title: The Stolen Earth
desc: The return of an old enemy leaves Earth along with 26 other planets stolen from their places. As the Doctor and Donna look for the whereabouts of Earth, former companions of the Doctor assemble a resistance against the new Dalek Empire.

title: Journey's End
desc: In the wake of Davros' threat to destroy the existence of the Universe itself, the Doctor's companions unite to stop the Dalek empire. Which one will die by the prophecies and what will the fate be for the Doctor?

title: The Eleventh Hour
desc: With his TARDIS in ruins, the newly-regenerated Doctor with the help of Amy Pond must save the world in less than twenty minutes from galactic policemen known as the Atraxi.

title: The Beast Below
desc: The Doctor takes Amy to the future inside Starship UK, which contains in addition to British explorers, an intimidating race known as the Smilers.

title: Victory of the Daleks
desc: The TARDIS takes The Doctor and Amy to war-torn Britain in the middle of World War Two. Not only do they meet Winston Churchill himself, but the Doctor comes face to face once again with his greatest enemy of all.

title: The Time of Angels
desc: The Doctor and Amy emerge from the TARDIS to find the wreck of the Byzantium spaceship. Down below the Weeping Angels are stirring, but the Doctor has someone else to contend with; none other than the mysterious Professor River Song.

title: Flesh and Stone
desc: The Doctor, Amy, Dr. Song and the remaining soldiers manage to escape from the crashed ship and into the forest. The Angels attempt to create a rift in time and space much as the Doctor had found in Amy's room when they first met. Amy meanwhile is counting down from 10 minutes and the Doctor has determined that an Angel has taken over her mind.

title: The Vampires of Venice
desc: The Doctor and Amy cross swords in more ways than one with a horde of blood-sucking vampires in 16th century Venice.

title: Amy's Choice
desc: Five years after finally leaving the TARDIS Amy and Rory now married, live in the quiet little village of Leadworth. But everything is not what it would seem.

title: The Hungry Earth
desc: When a drill drills to deep into the earth, something that had been hibernating beneath the earth's crust is woken, and it's hungry for revenge.

title: Cold Blood
desc: The Silurians are awake, and Angry. The Silurians are preparing for war, A war that could decide who gets to live on earth, The Silurians or-the humans..

title: Vincent and the Doctor
desc: The Doctor and Amy travel back in time to meet Vincent Van Gogh and face an invisible monster that only the painter can see.

title: The Lodger
desc: After the TARDIS teleports without him, the doctor tries to find out what is stopping it from landing and traces it to a seemingly ordinary, two storey house.

title: The Pandorica Opens
desc: River Song returns to deliver The Doctor a serious warning from his allies: the mythical Pandorica, said to contain the most feared creature in the entire Universe, is opening.

title: The Big Bang
desc: The Pandorica opened, silence fell, and now planet Earth is left alone in the universe. Jumping through time, the doctor must figure out a way to bring back those who never were and save his friends from the collapse of reality.

title: A Christmas Carol
desc: on Christmas eve, The doctor travels into the past of a bitter old man who has the power to save Amy and Rory but doesn't want to save them, so that he doesn't grow up to be mean and bitter.

title: The Impossible Astronaut
desc: The Doctor, Amy, Rory and River Song are reunited in the Utah desert.

title: Day of the Moon
desc: The Doctor and his allies mount a rebellion against invaders who have been controlling humanity from the very beginning.

title: The Curse of the Black Spot
desc: The Doctor, Amy and Rory find themselves aboard a marooned pirate ship whose crew is being picked off one by one by a beautiful - and deadly - Siren.

title: The Doctor's Wife
desc: The Doctor is lured to a sentient asteroid outside of the Universe by a Time Lord distress signal and soon realises his TARDIS is in grave danger.

title: The Rebel Flesh
desc: A solar tsunami sends the TARDIS crew to an acid mining factory in the 22nd century, where a small team of workers come under attack from their doppelgangers.

title: The Almost People
desc: The gangers and humans battle for their lives as the factory crumbles and the Doctor tries to keep the peace - can everyone make it off the island alive?

title: A Good Man Goes to War
desc: A member of The Doctor's team has been abducted and he will call in every favor and maybe even go to war to get them back.

title: Let's Kill Hitler
desc: The search for Melody Pond brings the Doctor and his friends to Berlin in 1938, face-to-face with Adolf Hitler, River Song and a justice-serving, shapeshifting robot.

title: Night Terrors
desc: Receiving a powerful distress call from a terrified little boy, the Doctor and his friends soon find that the monsters in his cupboard are real - and deadly.

title: The Girl Who Waited
desc: Amy is trapped in a quarantine facility where time moves faster than in reality, while the Doctor is confined to the TARDIS. Can Rory save his wife in time?

title: The God Complex
desc: The Doctor, Amy and Rory become trapped in a hotel of horrors unable to escape and unable to find the TARDIS. The Doctor must save as many people as he can taking many twists and seeing his own worst fear.

title: Closing Time
desc: The Doctor makes one last stop before his death to see an old friend. But people are disappearing, there are reports of a silver rat and metal men are lurking in the shadows.

title: The Wedding of River Song
desc: April 22nd, 2011; 5:02pm. Having finally accepted his fate the Doctor travels to Lake Silencio for his final day. But one woman refuses to let time take its course.

title: The Doctor, the Widow and the Wardrobe
desc: It's Christmas Eve, 1938, when Madge Arwell comes to the aid of an injured Spaceman Angel as she cycles home. He promises to repay her kindness - all she has to do is make a wish. Three years later, a devastated Madge escapes war-torn London with her two children for a dilapidated house in Dorset. She is crippled with grief at the news her husband has been lost over the channel, but determined to give Lily and Cyril the best Christmas ever. The Arwells are surprised to be greeted by a madcap caretaker whose mysterious Christmas gift leads them into a magical wintry ...

title: Asylum of the Daleks
desc: Amy, Rory and the Doctor are reunited when they are kidnapped by the Daleks, who send them on a mission to destroy the most horrifying place in the universe- the asylum of the Daleks.

title: Dinosaurs on a Spaceship
desc: The doctor gathers some of his old friends to help him investigate an unmanned spaceship on a crash course to earth that when it collides, will destroy it, they soon discover the ship's precious and dangerous cargo- dinosaurs.

title: A Town Called Mercy
desc: The Doctor gets a Stetson (and a gun), and finds himself the reluctant Sheriff of a Western town under siege by a relentless cyborg who goes by the name of The Gunslinger. But who is he and what does he want?

title: The Power of Three
desc: Earth is suddenly visited by millions of small black cubes of unknown origin. The Doctor joins Amy, Rory and Rory's father, Brian, to help discover what these cubes bring for humanity.

title: The Angels Take Manhattan
desc: After Rory has an encounter with a weeping angel, the doctor and Amy travel to 1930's New York to save him, but they soon discover that the weeping angels have taken over Manhattan, and soon, maybe, the world.

title: The Snowmen
desc: London, 1892. Snow is evolving, turning into icy monstrosities, but this is no concern for the Doctor who has given up trying to save the universe, leaving it to a clever young governess named Clara to save the day.

title: The Bells of Saint John
desc: The doctor finds Clara in present day, where they work together to solve the mystery of people disappearing which as it turns out, has a sinister link to WiFi.

title: The Rings of Akhaten
desc: The doctor takes Clara to the rings of Akheten, A partly destroyed planet, where a religious ceremony is about to be carried out, but a darkness is stirring, a hungry darkness that could consume the rings of Akhetan and the universe.

title: Cold War
desc: The doctor and Clara find themselves on a Russian cold war submarine that is falling to the bottom of the ocean because of an attack by a rogue Martian warrior, that 's still aboard.

title: Hide
desc: The Doctor and Clara arrive at a supposedly haunted mansion where they find a ghost hunter and a psychic who are on the search for a legendary ghost known as 'the witch of the well'

title: Journey to the Centre of the TARDIS
desc: After the TARDIS is caught accidentally by an outer space trash collector, Clara is trapped deep inside of it where she finds herself on a journey through the doctor's past and her future.

title: The Crimson Horror
desc: When they find a picture of the Doctor in a recently dead man's eye, it's up to Madame Vastra, Jenny and Strax to save The Doctor and find out what sinister secrets are going on at Sweetsville, Yorkshire.

title: Nightmare in Silver
desc: The Doctor takes Clara and the children she babysits to a rundown amusement park in space where Cybermen are hiding, and ready to invade the most precious place in the universe, The Doctor's mind.

title: The Name of the Doctor
desc: The Doctor's friends are being kidnapped, which leads him to the fields of Trenzalore, where his greatest secret will be revealed and Clara's mystery will be solved.

title: The Time of the Doctor
desc: The Doctor's worst enemies, The Daleks, The Cybermen, The Angels and The Silence, return, as the doctor's eleventh life comes to a close, and his twelfth life begins.

title: Deep Breath
desc: When the newly-regenerated doctor arrives in Victorian London, he finds a dinosaur rampant in the Thames and a spate of deadly spontaneous combustions.

title: Into the Dalek
desc: The Doctor's greatest enemy surrounds a rebel ship. To save everyone, he and Clara must choose to venture into the most dangerous place in the universe. The Doctor is forced to examine his conscience and ask if he is a good man.

title: Robot of Sherwood
desc: In Sherwood Forest, the Doctor uncovers a sinister alien plot and forms an alliance with Robin Hood. With Nottingham at stake, the Doctor must decide who is real and who is fake.

title: Listen
desc: When ghosts of past and future crowd into their lives, The Doctor and Clara are thrown into an adventure that takes them to the very end of the universe.

title: Time Heist
desc: The Doctor and Clara wake up in a room with two other people, unable to remember how they got there. As it turns out Someone known as the Architect has employed them to Break into the Universe's most secure bank.

title: The Caretaker
desc: The terrifying Skovox Blitzer is ready to destroy all humanity - but worse, and any second now, Danny Pink and the Doctor are going to meet.

title: Kill the Moon
desc: In the near future, the Doctor and Clara find themselves on a space shuttle making a suicide mission to the Moon. Crash-landing on the lunar surface they find the most terrible things.

title: Mummy on the Orient Express
desc: On the most beautiful train in history, speeding amongst the stars of the future, a deadly and immortal creature is stalking the passengers.

title: Flatline
desc: A problem happens with the Tardis, trapping the Doctor inside and leaving Clara to fend for herself against a two dimensional enemy.

title: In the Forest of the Night
desc: One morning in London, and every city and town in the world, the human race wakes up to the most surprising invasion yet: the trees have moved back in. Everywhere, in every land, a forest has grown and taken back the Earth.

title: Dark Water
desc: In the mysterious world of the Nethersphere, plans have been drawn. Old friends and old enemies manoeuvre around the Doctor, and an impossible choice is looming over him.

title: Death in Heaven
desc: With Cybermen on the streets of London, old friends unite against old enemies and the Doctor takes to the air in a startling new role. As the Doctor faces his greatest challenge, sacrifices must be made before the day is won.

title: Last Christmas
desc: The Doctor and Clara face their Last Christmas. Trapped on an Arctic base, under attack from terrifying creatures, who are you going to call? Santa Claus!

title: The Magician's Apprentice
desc: When the skies of Earth are frozen by a mysterious alien force, Clara needs her friend, the Doctor. But where is he and what is he hiding from?

title: The Witch's Familiar
desc: Trapped and alone in a terrifying Dalek city, the Doctor is at the heart of an evil Empire; no sonic, no TARDIS, nobody to help. With his greatest temptation before him, can the Doctor resist? And will there be mercy?

title: Under the Lake
desc: The Doctor and Clara find themselves on a underwater station where the crew live in fear of deadly ghosts which have taken over the station.

title: Before the Flood
desc: In a town that never was, the Doctor and his friends are being stalked by a mysterious figure. With the past and future in the balance, can the Doctor stop the evil Fisher King? And more importantly, who composed Beethoven's 5th.

title: The Girl Who Died
desc: In a Viking village, a girl named Ashildr is about to make a desperate mistake. The Mire are the deadliest mercenaries in the galaxy, famed for showing no mercy and Ashildr has just declared war on them. The Doctor and Clara have 12 hours to turn a peaceful village into strong fighters, ready for the deadly Mire.

title: The Woman Who Lived
desc: England, 1651. A deadly highwayman known only as 'The Knightmare' plagues the dark streets of London, his fire-breathing accomplice by his side. There's something clearly more than human here, and that includes the loot as much as the outlaws. Who are these creatures, and are they enemies to be fought, or friends who might possibly save the Doctor from certain doom on the gallows?

title: The Zygon Invasion
desc: Zygons, a shape-shifting alien race, and humans live in peace together on earth, but a group of rogue zygons threaten the peace between humans and zygons.

title: The Zygon Inversion
desc: With the Zygons invading England, and UNIT neutralized, the Doctor stands alone to stop the Zygons from taking over the entire planet. But how can he stop the Zygons? And how can he save his friends?

title: Sleep No More
desc: Vision recovered from the wreckage of Le Verrier Space Station shows how the Doctor and Clara became entangled in a rescue mission. As the footage plays out, a horrifying secret is uncovered.

title: Face the Raven
desc: The Doctor and Clara are called back to Earth when Rigsy discovers a strange tattoo on the back of his neck that appears to be counting down to zero. Their investigation leads them to a hidden street in the middle of London, the discovery that Rigsy has been issued a death sentence, and one of them facing the choice of having to make the ultimate sacrifice; to face the Raven!

title: Heaven Sent
desc: Trapped in a world unlike any other he has seen, the Doctor faces the greatest challenge of his many lives. One final test. And he must face it alone...

title: Hell Bent
desc: If you took everything from him, betrayed him, trapped him, and broke both his hearts... how far might the Doctor go? Returning to Gallifrey, the Doctor faces the Time Lords in a struggle that will take him to the end of time itself. Who is the Hybrid? And what is the Doctor's confession?

title: The Husbands of River Song
desc: When a crashed spaceship calls upon the Doctor for help, he finds himself recruited into River Song's squad and hurled into a chase across the galaxy.

title: The Return of Doctor Mysterio
desc: In New York, with brain-swapping aliens poised to attack, the Doctor and Nardole link up with an investigative reporter and a mysterious masked superhero known only as the Ghost. Can the Doctor save Manhattan? And what will be revealed when we see behind the mask?

title: The Pilot
desc: The Doctor and Nardole team up with a university student to take down a sinister life-mimicking alien.

title: Smile
desc: The Doctor brings Bill to a future human colony, where cute EmojiBots work as willing servants and make sure everybody's happy, but if they're not happy ,they're harvested, so Bill and The Doctor better smile, or else.

title: Thin Ice
desc: The Doctor and Bill visit London during the last of the River Thames frost fairs in February 1814. They soon discover that there is something under the ice which is causing people to disappear.

title: Knock Knock
desc: Bill is moving in with some friends and they've found the perfect house rented by the landlord. The wind blows, the floorboards creak and the Doctor thinks something is very wrong.

title: Oxygen
desc: When the Doctor, Bill and Nardole become trapped on a space station without oxygen, they discover the spacesuits are trying to kill them.

title: Extremis
desc: The Doctor is called by the Vatican to solve the mystery of a text called the Veritas, that when someone reads it dies soon after. But something is dwelling in the Vatican, and doesn't want the Veritas to be read.

title: The Pyramid at the End of the World
desc: A 5,000-year-old pyramid appears overnight, baffling everyone including the Doctor.

title: The Lie of the Land
desc: Earth is invaded and Bill is living alone in occupied Britain. The Doctor appears to be on the side of the enemy, flooding the airwaves with fake news. Bill and Nardole embark on a deadly mission to rescue the Doctor and lead the resistance against the new regime, whatever the cost.

title: Empress of Mars
desc: The Doctor, Bill and Nardole discover a tomb of the Queen of the Ice Warriors on Mars in 1881.

title: The Eaters of Light
desc: A long time ago, the Roman legion of the ninth vanished into the mists of Scotland. Bill has a theory about what happened, and the Doctor has a time machine. But when they arrive in ancient Aberdeenshire, what they find is a far greater threat than any army. In a cairn, on a hillside, is a doorway leading to the end of the world.

title: World Enough and Time
desc: Trapped on a giant spaceship, caught in the event horizon of a black hole, he witnesses the death of someone he is pledged to protect. Are events already out of control?

title: The Doctor Falls
desc: The Doctor makes a final stand against an army of Cybermen to protect a tiny band of humans from destruction.

title: Twice Upon a Time
desc: The Twelfth Doctor, still refusing to change, goes on a last adventure with the First Doctor.

title: The Woman Who Fell to Earth
desc: In a South Yorkshire city, Ryan Sinclair, Yasmin Khan and Graham O'Brien are about to have their lives changed forever, as a mysterious woman, unable to remember her own name, falls from the night sky.

title: The Ghost Monument
desc: Still reeling from their first encounter, can the Doctor and her new friends stay alive long enough, in a hostile alien environment, to solve the mystery of Desolation? And just who are Angstrom and Epzo?

title: Rosa
desc: Montgomery, Alabama, 1955. The Doctor and her friends find themselves in the Deep South of America. As they encounter a seamstress by the name of Rosa Parks, they begin to wonder whether someone is attempting to change history.

title: Arachnids in the UK
desc: The Doctor, Yaz, Graham, and Ryan find their way back to Yorkshire only to find something is stirring amidst the eight-legged arachnid population of Sheffield.

title: The Tsuranga Conundrum
desc: Injured and stranded in the wilds of a far-flung galaxy, The Doctor, Yaz, Graham, and Ryan must band together with a group of strangers to survive against one of the universe's most deadly - and unusual - creatures.

title: Demons of the Punjab
desc: Yasmin travels in time to visit her grandmother during her youth in the partition of India, but everyone gets caught up in the tragic bloodshed of that era.

title: Kerblam!
desc: A mysterious message arrives in a package addressed to the Doctor, leading her, Graham, Yaz and Ryan to investigate the warehouse moon orbiting Kandoka, and the home of the galaxy's largest retailer.

title: The Witchfinders
desc: Arriving in 17th Century Lancashire, the TARDIS team become embroiled in a witch trial. With the arrival of King James I, the hunt for witches intensifies. However, could something more dangerous be at play? Can the Doctor, Graham, Yaz and Ryan keep the populace of Bilehurst Cragg safe from the forces surrounding the land?

title: It Takes You Away
desc: On the edge of a Norwegian fjord, in the present day, The Doctor, Ryan, Graham and Yaz discover a boarded-up cottage and a girl named Hanne in need of their help. What has happened here? What monster lurks in the woods around the cottage - and beyond?

title: The Battle of Ranskoor Av Kolos
desc: Answering nine separate distress calls, the Doctor and team arrive on the remnants of a brutal battlefield on the planet Ranskoor Av Kolos. This planet has many secrets. An amnesiac commander? Mysterious mists? Who or what are the Ux? A deadly reckoning awaits the Doctor and team once they have the answers....

title: Resolution
desc: As the New Year begins, a terrifying evil is stirring from across the centuries of Earth's history. As the Doctor, Ryan, Graham and Yaz return home, will they be able to overcome the threat to planet Earth?

title: Spyfall: Part One
desc: When intelligence agents around the world come under attack from alien forces, MI6 turns to the only person who can help... The Doctor.

title: Spyfall: Part Two
desc: A terrifying plan to destroy humanity is about to reach fruition. Can the Doctor and her friends escape multiple traps and defeat a deadly alliance?

title: Orphan 55
desc: Having decided that everyone could do with a holiday, Graham accidentally teleports himself, the Doctor Yasmin and Ryan to a luxury resort for a spot of rest and relaxation. However, they discover the place where they are having a break is hiding a number of deadly secrets. What are the ferocious monsters that are attacking Tranquility Spa?

title: Nikola Tesla's Night of Terror
desc: The time: the earliest years of the 20th century. The place: New York City. Inventor Nikola Tesla is at war with his rival Thomas Edison. However, there's an even greater threat in their midst.

title: Fugitive of the Judoon
desc: Stomping their way into present-day Gloucester, the Judoon are on the hunt for someone on the run. Who is this fugitive? And why are these alien mercenaries after them?

title: Praxeus
desc: The Doctor and her friends split up to investigate multiple mysteries across planet Earth. What they find will threaten all of humanity.

title: Can You Hear Me?
desc: From ancient Syria to present day Sheffield, and out into the wilds of space, something is stalking the Doctor and infecting people's nightmares.

title: The Haunting of Villa Diodati
desc: Villa Diodati, 1816 - on a night that inspired Mary Shelley's Frankenstein. The plan was to spend the evening in the presence of literary greats - but the ghosts are all too real. And the Doctor is forced into an earth-shattering decision.

title: Ascension of the Cybermen
desc: In the far future, the Doctor and her friends face a brutal battle across the farthest reaches of space to protect the last of the human race against the deadly Cybermen.

title: The Timeless Children
desc: In the epic and emotional season finale, the Cybermen are on the march. As the last remaining humans are ruthlessly hunted down, Graham, Ryan and Yaz face a terrifying fight to survive. Civilisations fall. Others rise anew. Lies are exposed, truths are revealed, battles are fought, and for the Doctor - trapped and alone - nothing will ever be the same again.

title: Revolution of the Daleks
desc: Robertson returns, and inadvertently gives the mutant Dalek a chance to clone itself. The Doctor escapes from her alien prison with the help of an old friend, and returns to help.

title: Time Crash
desc: The Tenth Doctor meets one of his previous incarnations.

title: The Next Doctor
desc: The Doctor arrives in London on Christmas Eve in 1851 where he encounters the Cybermen and a man who claims he's a Time Lord called the Doctor.

title: Planet of the Dead
desc: A meeting in a London bus with jewel thief Lady Christina takes a turn for the worst for the Doctor when the bus takes a detour to a desert-like planet, where the deadly Swarm awaits.

title: The Waters of Mars
desc: In a Mars base the inhabitants are being infected by a mysterious water creature which takes over its victims. The Doctor is thrust into the middle of this catastrophe knowing a larger one is waiting around the corner.

title: A Ghost Story for Christmas
desc: This mini-story tells of the Weeping Angels and depicts their abduction of a young woman named Julia Hardwick.

title: The End of Time: Part One
desc: The Ood have given a warning to The Doctor. The Master is returning yet that is not the biggest threat. A darkness is coming which brings with it The End of Time.

title: The End of Time: Part Two
desc: With almost everyone on Earth now recast in his image, The Master controls the Earth. He's shocked however when he realises one person hasn't changed; Donna Noble. The Doctor soon understands what the pounding in the Master's head is; it's the Time Lords, who are trying to return and re-establish Gallifrey. If they succeed, it'll mean the Last Great Time War will re-start, and all the horrors which came with it. In order to stop Rasillon's mad plan, the Doctor must make a choice. Finally, the Ood's prophecy for the Doctor becomes true, and he takes the TARDIS on a ...

title: Prequel to the Impossible Astronaut
desc: The new series of Doctor Who begins with The Impossible Astronaut. But before that we have a short scene written by Steven Moffat that reveals a little of what we can expect from the adventure and what the Doctor will be facing!

title: Prequel to the Curse of the Black Spot
desc: The third episode of Doctor Who is a scary, action-packed adventure called The Curse of the Black Spot. What evil lurks for the crew in the darkness? Come aboard and watch the spine-chilling prequel to The Curse of the Black Spot.

title: Prequel to A Good Man Goes to War
desc: As the Doctor prepares to face his darkest hour, key players conspire and a grim warning is given...

title: Prequel to Let's Kill Hitler
desc: The battle of Demon's Run has been fought but the stakes are now higher than ever! As the TARDIS crosses the universe, the Doctor receives a heart-breaking message from Amy... Their adventure continues in this brilliant Prequel written by Steven Moffat.

title: Prequel to the Wedding of River Song
desc: The Doctor's time is running out and he faces a date with death by the shores of Lake Silencio - Meanwhile, in the presence of an old enemy, we hear a prophesy that will change everything.

title: Prequel to the Doctor, the Widow and the Wardrobe
desc: Written by Steven Moffat and starring Matt Smith as the Doctor, this exciting Prequel shows what was happening to the Time Lord moments before the explosive start of the Christmas Special!

title: Prequel to Asylum of the Daleks
desc: The Doctor receives a message from a mysterious hooded stranger - a woman called Darla Von Karlsen wants to meet him...

title: The Making of the Gunslinger
desc: A detailed explanation of the creation of the Gunslinger and all the factors that went into selecting the "participants".

title: The Great Detective
desc: Matt and Jenna introduce the Doctor Who Christmas Prequel, The Great Detective, in which Vastra, Jenny and Strax try to persuade the grumpy Doctor to engage again.

title: Vastra Investigates: A Christmas Prequel
desc: Madame Vastra finishes a case with Scotland Yard, but continues to worry about The Doctor.

title: The Bells of Saint John: A Prequel
desc: A look at the opening of the first episode of the new season, The Bells of Saint John.

title: The Battle of Demon's Run: Two Days Later
desc: In the aftermath of the battle of Demons Run, a battle-scarred Strax lies dying on the floor - or has he just fainted...

title: She Said, He Said: A Prequel
desc: The Doctor and Clara each deliver a separate monologue summing up their thoughts on each other before the events of "The Name of the Doctor."

title: Clarence and the Whispermen
desc: The Whispermen visits Clarence in his cell.

title: Clara and the Tardis
desc: Clara has a conversation with the TARDIS, and encounters a surprise.

title: Rain Gods
desc: The Doctor and River are about to be sacrificed to the Rain Gods of an unknown planet and the Doctor must come up with a plan to save themselves.

title: The Inforarium
desc: In the Doctor's quest to delete all information on him in the universe, he visits the Inforarium, a universal database, in hope to erase himself from it.

title: The Night of the Doctor
desc: With the aid of the Sisterhood of Karn, the Eighth Doctor regenerates into the War Doctor.

title: The Day of the Doctor
desc: In 2013, something terrible is awakening in London's National Gallery; in 1562, a murderous plot is afoot in Elizabethan England; and somewhere in space an ancient battle reaches its devastating conclusion.

title: Prologue
desc: Doctor Who Season 9 starts here with this prologue to Episode 1, "The Magician's Apprentice".

title: The Doctor's Meditation
desc: The Doctor contemplates a journey to see an old acquaintance and digs a well.

title: Friend from the Future
desc: The Doctor and Bill are chased by a group of Daleks in a short introductory video to present Bill, the new companion, to audiences for the first time.
